devdoc.author: ronmedina@superiorblocks.io
devdoc.details: Multisig Wallet Smart Contract where multiple signatures/approvals  are needed for an outgoing transfer to take place. Anyone can deposit funds.  As soon as we want to spend funds, it requires the specified number of approvals.

approve(uint256).details: A method to approve a transfer by an owner.  It does the following:  - Sets your approval for one of the transfer requests.  - Updates the Transfer object.  - Updates the mapping to record the approval for the msg.sender.  - When the amount of approvals for a transfer has reached the limit, this function sends the transfer to the recipient.  - An owner is not allowed to vote twice.  - An owner is not allowed to vote on a tranfer request that has already been sent.

createTransfer(uint256,address).details: A method that creates an instance of the Transfer struct and push it into the  transferRequests array

deposit().details: A method to make a deposit.

getBalance().details: A method to get the sender's balance.

getTransferRequests().details: A method to get transfer requests array information.

documentation.text:
@dev A method to approve a transfer by an owner.  It does the following:
  - Sets your approval for one of the transfer requests.
  - Updates the Transfer object.
  - Updates the mapping to record the approval for the msg.sender.
  - When the amount of approvals for a transfer has reached the limit, this function sends the transfer to the recipient.
  - An owner is not allowed to vote twice.
  - An owner is not allowed to vote on a tranfer request that has already been sent.
